  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 6 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 15 high, 10 medium, 13 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT); plus 13 other bases. 10 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, thunderstorm / convective risk and mist  — most notably around Vilnius (VNO/EYVI), London Luton (LTN/EGGW) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD). Network hotspots: Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Olsztyn-Mazury (SZY/EPSY), Stockholm Skavsta (NYO/ESKN), Kaunas (KUN/EYKA), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) and 1 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Olsztyn-Mazury (SZY/EPSY), Kaunas (KUN/EYKA), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) and 9 others.",
